external_knowledge:
- "Grand league of players" refers to the teams in the database;
- "Strong roster of at least three stars" indicates teams with at least three players;
- "Average wealth" refers to the average salary of the players on the team;
- "Financial might" is a metaphor for the average salary, which is used to rank the teams.

- "Shining stars" refers to players with exceptional performance scores;
- "Outshine their teammates" means their performance score is greater than the average performance score of their team;
- "Outshine the season's average" means their performance score is greater than the average performance score of their season;
- "Command a contract worth more than a million dollars" means their total contract value (salary + bonus) is greater than $1,000,000.

- 'Combined salary and bonus' refers to the total earnings of a player;
- 'Eclipse the average earnings of their teammates' means the player's total earnings are above the average earnings of players in their team;
- 'Boast the highest batting average' refers to the team with the player having the highest batting average among all players in the team.

- Performance categories include batting average, hits, runs, RBIs, doubles, triples, and home runs;
- The query ensures the player is ranked first in all these categories;
- The player's contract value is also considered.

- 'assembled a lineup' refers to the team's composition of players;
- 'contract value' refers to the annual salary of the players;
- 'shines brighter than the $500,000 mark' means the average salary is greater than $500,000.

- 'Shining stars' refers to players who are among the top 3 in their team for hits, runs, and RBIs;
- 'Hits' are the total number of times a player successfully reaches a base;
- 'Runs' are the total number of times a player scores a point by reaching home plate;
- 'RBIs' (Runs Batted In) are the total number of runs scored due to a player's batting.

- "Top three highest-paid players" refers to players within each team who are ranked in the top 3 based on their batting average and have a salary greater than $400,000;
- "Average batting average exceeding a stellar 0.35" means the average of the batting averages of these top three players is greater than 0.35;
- "Shining cities" refers to the cities where the teams are based.
